HEADWORD: carriage bolt
<hw>carriage bolt</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a type of bolt threaded only
at the end opposite the head, used mostly for fastening pieces of timber
together, and inserted into pre-drilled holes.</def>⟦br⟧
